In recognition of the provision of uncompensated care by Montebello and to assist with the capital financial needs of Montebello specified as part of the transfer under § 13-402 of this subtitle, the State shall pay the Medical System Corporation:
In fiscal year 1993, $6,129,942;
In fiscal year 1994, $5,500,000;
In fiscal year 1995, $5,000,000;
In fiscal year 1996, $5,000,000;
In fiscal year 1997, $5,000,000; and
In each fiscal year thereafter, an amount jointly agreed upon by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene and the Medical System Corporation and calculated to enable the Medical System Corporation to continue to provide uncompensated care by Montebello and to assist with the capital financial needs of Montebello specified as part of the transfer under § 13-402 of this subtitle.
